http://www.oracle.com/technetwork/topics/intel-macsoft-096467.html 
Download  a basic version from the link.

Put all files in the folder that has been downloaded into 
/usr/local/lib
（not the folder itself，but all files directly into the path: 
/usr/local/lib）

Then in terminal cd to steam-recommendation:
npm install oracledb

If access is denied, in a new terminal：
sudo spctl --master-disable
allow Mac to access all files downloaded from website
